#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:1
msgid "Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:3
msgid ""
"This page describes the tooling used during development of this project. It "
"also serves as a reference for the various commands that you would use when "
"working on this project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:7
msgid ""
"This project uses the [GitHub Flow] for collaboration. The codebase contains "
"Python code, [Jinja2]-based HTML pages, [Sass] stylesheets and Javascript "
"code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:9
msgid "[nox] is used for automating development tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:10
msgid ""
"[Webpack]-based build pipeline is used to process the Sass and Javascript "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:11
msgid ""
"[sphinx-autobuild] is used to provide live-reloading pages when working on "
"the theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:12
msgid "[pre-commit] is used for running the linters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:14
msgid "Initial Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:16
msgid ""
"To work on this project, you need to have git 2.17+ and Python 3.6+. You "
"also need to be on a platform that is officially supported by NodeJS 16."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:18
msgid "Clone this project using git:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:20
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo.git\n"
"cd furo\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:25
msgid "Install the project's development workflow runner:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:27
msgid "pip install nox\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:31
msgid "You're all set for working on this project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:33
msgid "Commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:35
msgid "Code Linting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:37
msgid "nox -s lint\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:41
msgid "Run the linters, as configured with [pre-commit]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:43
msgid "Local Development Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:45
msgid "nox -s docs-live\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:49
msgid ""
"Serve this project's documentation locally, using [sphinx-autobuild]. This "
"will open the generated documentation page in your browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:51
msgid ""
"The server also watches for changes made to the documentation (`docs/`) or "
"theme (`src/`), which will trigger a rebuild. Once the build is completed, "
"server will automagically reload any open pages using livereload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:54
msgid "My workflow, when I'm working on this theme, is along the lines of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:56
msgid "Run this command, and wait for the browser window to open."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:57
msgid "<kbd>alt</kbd>+<kbd>tab</kbd> gets me back to my text editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:57 ../../../contributing/workflow.md:59
#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:61
msgid "<kbd>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:57 ../../../contributing/workflow.md:59
#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:61
msgid "</kbd>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:58
msgid "Make changes to some files and save those changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:59
msgid "<kbd>alt</kbd>+<kbd>tab</kbd> switches to the browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:60
msgid "After a small delay, the change is reflected in the browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:61
msgid ""
"If I want to make more changes, <kbd>alt</kbd>+<kbd>tab</kbd> and I'm back "
"to my text editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:62
msgid "Repeat the previous 4 steps until happy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:64
msgid "\\- @pradyunsg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:67
msgid "Documentation Generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:69
msgid "nox -s docs\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:73
msgid ""
"Generate the documentation for Furo into the `build/docs` folder. This "
"(mostly) does the same thing as `nox -s docs-live`, except it invokes "
"`sphinx-build` instead of [sphinx-autobuild]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:75
msgid "Release process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:77
msgid "Update the changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:78
msgid "Run `nox -s release`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:79
msgid "Once that command succeeds, you're done!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:81
msgid "Installing directly from GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:83
msgid ""
"There are times when you might want to install the in-development version of "
"Furo (mostly for testing that a fix actually does fix things)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:85
msgid ""
"This can be done by directly telling pip to install from Furo from GitHub. "
"You likely want to install from a zip archive, to avoid cloning the entire "
"Git history:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:87
msgid ""
"pip install https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo/archive/refs/heads/main.zip\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:91
msgid "Dependency management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:93
msgid ""
"This project has dependencies managed via [pre-commit], Python and NodeJS. "
"We regularly update these dependencies to ensure that the project's "
"development workflow is up-to-date. Aside from the risks of functional "
"behavior changes in dependencies, the updates for pre-commit and NodeJS can "
"be done by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:95
msgid ""
"pre-commit autoupdate\n"
"npm update\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/workflow.md:100
msgid ""
"The Python dependencies are un-pinned, other than Sphinx which requires "
"manual intervention to investigate the updates."
msgstr ""
